  "title": "North Indian Curry and Tandoor Business Development Manager",
  "description": "<p>A Web Portal Business Development Manager</p><p>drives growth by identifying new market opportunities, building strategic partnerships, and increasing user engagement for digital platforms</p><p>. They are responsible for generating leads, developing marketing strategies, analyzing market trends, and managing client relationships to expand the portal's reach and revenue.</p><p>Key responsibilities and qualifications typically include:</p><ul><li><strong>Strategic Planning:</strong> Creating and implementing strategies to increase revenue and improve platform performance.</li><li><strong>Business Development:</strong> Identifying, pursuing, and closing new business opportunities, partnerships, and, if applicable, advertising partnerships.</li><li><strong>Market Research:</strong> Analyzing competitors, industry trends, and market demands to enhance the web portal's offerings.</li><li><strong>Client Relationship Management:</strong> Building and maintaining strong relationships with clients, partners, and stakeholders.</li><li><strong>Performance Metrics:</strong> Defining and tracking KPIs to measure the success of initiatives and reporting on performance.</li><li><strong>Collaboration:</strong> Working closely with marketing, sales, and product teams to align strategies and improve user experience. </li></ul><p><strong>Key Skills & Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Strategic Thinking:</strong> Ability to identify long-term opportunities.</li><li><strong>Communication & Negotiation:</strong> Excellent interpersonal skills for building partnerships.</li><li><strong>Analytical Skills:</strong> Capability to interpret data and market research.</li><li><strong>Experience:</strong> Proven experience in business development, sales, or digital marketing.</li><li><strong>Technical Knowledge:</strong> Familiarity with digital platforms, web technologies, and CRM software. </li></ul>",
